The course deals with the 5 topics:
MINA JA ÜLIKOOL (Me and my studies)
MIDA SA EILE TEGID? (What did you do yesterday? Verbs)
SÕBRAD JA NAABRID (Friends and Neighbors. Adjectives)
INIMESED: VÄLIMUS JA RIIDED (People: appearance and clothes)
KODU: MAJA JA TUBA (Home, house and room. Postpositions)Objectives/eesmärkid:  This is a short continuation course for beginners that develops the  students' basic knowledge of the Estonian grammatical stuctures and spoken language. The aim of the course is to practise the basics of Estonian grammar and vocabulary. The intended outcome of the course is the language level A1.2 (Basic User) in all the language skills.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  On completion of the course the students will be able:
*	to understand and use the basic Estonian cases (grammatical cases, local cases)   
        both in singular and plural;
*	to conjugate the verbs in the present and past tenses (imperfect, perfect);
*	to compare the adjectives;
*	to use the cardinal and ordinal numbers;
*	to communicate in everyday situations in the street, in a shop, at a restaurant and socialize in a group, to 
        introduce her/himself, to talk about weather, plans, eating habits and home. Is able to describe and 
        compare things, persons and situations.
